screens.screen_desc: The screenshot shows the Uber app interface. At the top, there is a search bar with a magnifying glass icon and the text "Enter pickup point," along with a button labeled "Now" with a clock icon. Below the search bar, there are two promotional banners. The first banner on a green background asks, "Want better pick-ups?" with an illustration of a person looking through binoculars. The second banner on a light purple background says, "Ready? Then let's roll. Ride with Uber" with an image of a person opening a car door. At the bottom of the screen, there is a navigation bar with icons labeled "Home," "Services," "Activity," and "Account." The time displayed at the top of the screen is 8:46 AM, and various status icons are visible, including battery, signal strength, and VPN.

The screenshot shows a ride-hailing app interface with the title "Plan your ride." There is an option to select the pickup time, currently set to "Pickup now." Below that, there are fields to enter the pickup location and destination ("Where to?"). Additional options include "Search in a different city," "Set location on map," and "Saved places." The interface also includes a back arrow in the top left corner and various icons at the bottom of the screen.

screens.screen_desc: The screenshot shows a mobile app interface titled "Saved places." There are three options listed: "Add Home" with a house icon, "Add Work" with a briefcase icon, and "Add a new place" with a plus icon. The top left corner has a back arrow for navigation. The status bar at the top displays the time (8:54 AM), various notification icons, and battery status.

A mobile screen displaying a "Set location on map" interface. At the top, the time is 8:54 AM, and various status icons are visible, including notifications, Bluetooth, VPN, signal strength, Wi-Fi, and battery level. Below the location setting prompt, there is a search bar with a back arrow on the left. The on-screen keyboard is visible at the bottom, featuring a background image of a night sky with stars and a lit tent. The keyboard includes standard keys, a microphone icon, a settings icon, and a smiley face icon. The keyboard is labeled "Laban Key."

flow_desc: The user requests to save their work address. The process begins with tapping the "Enter pickup point" on the Uber app interface, followed by selecting "Saved places." Next, the user taps "Add Work" to initiate adding the work address. The user then inputs the work address in the provided text field. After entering the desired work location, such as "Washington Hilton," the user proceeds by tapping the location icon to finalize the save process. Each step is carefully navigated within the app's interface, making it a seamless experience in designating a work address for future rides.
